Sure! Here is how to add Edit and Delete buttons to your Active Items table in Create.cshtml.

I will assume your controller already has:

Edit(int id)

Delete(int id) or DeleteConfirm(int id)


If not, I can generate them for you.


---

‚úÖ Updated Table with Edit & Delete Buttons

Add this to Create.cshtml, replacing your current table:

<h3 class="mt-4">Active Items</h3>

<table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Control No</th>
            <th>Item Name</th>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Quantity</th>
            <th>Status</th>
            <th>Warranty Expiration</th>
            <th style="width: 130px;">Actions</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        @foreach (var item in ViewBag.ActiveItems)
        {
            <tr>
                <td>@item.ControlNo</td>
                <td>@item.ItemName</td>
                <td>@item.CategoryName</td> <!-- if you are using JOIN -->
                <td>@item.Quantity</td>
                <td>@item.Status</td>
                <td>@item.WarrantyExpiration?.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd")</td>

                <td>
                    <a asp-controller="Item"
                       asp-action="Edit"
                       asp-route-id="@item.ItemID"
                       class="btn btn-sm btn-primary">
                        Edit
                    </a>

                    <a asp-controller="Item"
                       asp-action="Delete"
                       asp-route-id="@item.ItemID"
                       class="btn btn-sm btn-danger"
                       onclick="return confirm('Are you sure you want to delete this item?');">
                        Delete
                    </a>
                </td>
            </tr>
        }
    </tbody>
</table>


---

üìù Notes

‚úî Works with your existing stored procedures

The buttons simply call:

/Item/Edit/ID

/Item/Delete/ID


‚úî Auto-confirm delete

The alert prevents accidental deletion:

onclick="return confirm('Are you sure you want to delete this item?');"

‚úî Doesn't affect the Create form above

This table stays below the form, as you wanted.


