Got it! üëç
You want to add a table below your Create Item form that shows all records from tbl_items where Status = 'Active'.

I will give you:

‚úî Controller update

‚úî SQL to get Active Items

‚úî Razor code to display the table BELOW your Create form

‚úî Works with your existing stored-procedure setup



---

‚úÖ 1. Controller Update (ItemController.cs)

In your Create GET action, after LoadCategories();, load Active Items:

public IActionResult Create()
{
    LoadCategories();

    // LOAD ACTIVE ITEMS
    var activeItems = _context.Items
        .FromSqlRaw("SELECT * FROM tbl_items WHERE Status = 'Active'")
        .ToList();

    ViewBag.ActiveItems = activeItems;

    return View();
}

This will pass the active items to your Create view.


---

‚úÖ 2. Add Active Items Table in Create.cshtml

Place this BELOW your form, exactly as you requested:

<h3 class="mt-4">Active Items</h3>

<table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Control No</th>
            <th>Item Name</th>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Quantity</th>
            <th>Status</th>
            <th>Warranty Expiration</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        @foreach (var item in ViewBag.ActiveItems)
        {
            <tr>
                <td>@item.ControlNo</td>
                <td>@item.ItemName</td>
                <td>@item.CategoryID</td>
                <td>@item.Quantity</td>
                <td>@item.Status</td>
                <td>@item.WarrantyExpiration</td>
            </tr>
        }
    </tbody>
</table>

‚úî Table appears right below the Create form
‚úî Shows only items where Status = 'Active'
‚úî Automatically updates each time the Create page reloads


