üìå 3. OPTIONAL (Better Display for Category Name)

If you want the Category Name instead of CategoryID, change SQL:

SELECT i.*, c.CategoryName 
FROM tbl_items i
LEFT JOIN tbl_Category c ON i.CategoryID = c.CategoryID
WHERE i.Status = 'Active'

Then update your controller:

var activeItems = _context.Items
    .FromSqlRaw(@"SELECT i.*, c.CategoryName 
                  FROM tbl_items i
                  LEFT JOIN tbl_Category c ON i.CategoryID = c.CategoryID
                  WHERE i.Status = 'Active'")
    .ToList();

ViewBag.ActiveItems = activeItems;

Then update table:

<td>@item.CategoryName</td>


